{
  "stem": "10181.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was the first major thing what I noticed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, like I said, the Germans were there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And once in a while, I don't know where they went to, but there were big convoys going through, you know, the army convoys on-- on the main road.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But this was only real sign of the war, but there were other things too.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were the nightly air raids, which started to get worse in '41, '42.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The British used to bomb at night, and the Americans by day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I knew that even then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The British liked to fly at night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Americans didn't like to fly at night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This I didn't know at the time, but I knew the British flew at night and the Americans by day because-- I found this out because the planes got shot down, you know, and that's how I found out who-- who was who.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Our little village, Dinxperlo, was right on the border.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was almost cut in half by big barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On the other side was a German-- little German village, and it was the beginning of the [? rural ?] area, OK?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Heavy industrialized area, which in '41, '42 was a main target of the Allies.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And apparently, the way it used to-- they-- they used to sort of assemble above us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They used to come from England, the airplanes, and used to assemble in-- not just above us, but in a general area and then continue.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They came from three different directions apparently, and at the same time, this also was-- the Germans came from the-- from-- from their own air fields and tried to shoot the planes down.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Plus, there was anti-aircraft guns in the area too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Heavy, very heavy.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was-- the post-- the-- one of the big buildings in the village was a post office.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "On top of the post office was the-- this air raid siren, and the air raid siren used to take their cue, I think, from-- from Germany.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They used to hear the sirens in Germany so they [? knew ?] [? system. ?] We used to hear them also in the distance, and then-- then that siren went off.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And especially at night, it-- if it wasn't so dangerous, it would be like a sound and light show because you saw the-- the-- what do you call them.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The lights-- you know, the-- what do you call the lights which came from the ground into the air?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Search lights.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Search lights, right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the search lights, big search lights, tried to pick out the planes, OK, in the sky, and then they would shoot-- try to shoot them from the ground.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then the sky was crisscrossed with search lights, OK?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then you saw also some battles, you know, at night, and shooting.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You could see that because apparently these were like trace-- like tracer bullets which left signs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, in time, airplanes used to crash in our area quite a lot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, there were some nights when there were very heavy air raids.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Again, this is something which I didn't know at the time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was, like, 1,000 planes at the time when they-- when they attacked Cologne.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I-- I remember counting one night 15, 16 planes which crashed in our-- in our general area, and a lot of bombs fell.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why did the bombs fall?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't bomb us really, but if a plane was hit, they used to jettison the bombs in order to make it lighter.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe they could make it back to-- to England, so they jettisoned, where-- wherever they could.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they used to fall on our village, or the next village, or in-- or Grossenbrode in Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And luckily, like I said, the houses were sort of spaced out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It wasn't-- it wasn't a heavily built area, so a lot of the bombs used to fall into open fields.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some, of course, also fell on houses, and it came to that kind of situation where almost every night, we were up.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At the beginning, I used to sleep.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I used to hear it in my sleep.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was-- the bombing was so heavy, I used to hear it in my sleep.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everything used to shake, but I used to sleep though.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, my mom-- my sister used to wake me up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She was afraid and used to wake me up, and we used to sit downstairs and-- and-- to wait for whatever.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that's when I used to start going out and see what was happening.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
